MiniSpec
========

MiniSpec is a small library built on top of Test::Unit to provide rspec
syntax for systems where rspec may not be available (such as old versions
of macruby, or when it's just not feasible to run rspec).

Supported Features
==================

- context/describe
- it
- before, after (always run before each)
- should, should_not
- be_true, be_false, be_nil
- be(_an?)_.*
- running(&block)
- include
- change
- eql
- raise_error
